# WHAT IT IS
#   gofaces is the **reference Go-native ONNX face-detection CLI**
#   — a typed minimal end-to-end demonstration of running a typed
#   pre-trained YOLO-family face-detection neural network from
#   typed Go without any typed Python runtime, typed CUDA-toolkit
#   install, or typed external typed inference-server dependency.
#   Use cases:
#
#     • **Edge inference**             typed face detection inside
#                                      a typed Go-based edge
#                                      pipeline (typed IoT
#                                      cameras, typed embedded
#                                      vision systems) without
#                                      typed shipping Python +
#                                      OpenCV
#     • **Pipeline integration**       typed face-bounding-box
#                                      output piped into typed
#                                      downstream typed CV stages
#                                      (typed face recognition,
#                                      typed anonymization /
#                                      blurring, typed analytics)
#     • **Educational reference**      typed showcase of typed
#                                      ONNX-model loading + typed
#                                      Gorgonia tensor handling +
#                                      typed image preprocessing
#                                      in typed idiomatic Go
#     • **Privacy-preserving face
#       blurring**                     typed bounding-box mask
#                                      output (typed `--output`
#                                      PNG mask) suitable for
#                                      typed per-face overlay /
#                                      blur / pixelation in typed
#                                      downstream image-processing
#                                      pipelines
#
#   Workflow:
#     1. Operator downloads a typed YOLO-family face-detection
#        ONNX model (the typed default path is
#        `../model/model.onnx`;  typed pre-trained model files
#        ship alongside the typed source tree)
#     2. Operator invokes `gofaces --img input.jpg --output
#        boxes.png`
#     3. gofaces loads the typed ONNX model into the typed
#        gorgonnx Gorgonia-backed inference graph
#     4. gofaces preprocesses the typed input JPEG into the
#        typed `[1, 3, 416, 416]` typed YOLO-input typed tensor
#        (typed `gofaces.GetTensorFromImage(img)`)
#     5. gofaces invokes the typed `backend.Run()` typed forward
#        pass
#     6. gofaces postprocesses the typed `[1, 125, 13, 13]` typed
#        YOLO-output typed tensor into typed bounding boxes via
#        typed `gofaces.ProcessOutput()` + typed `gofaces.
#        Sanitize()` (typed Non-Maximum-Suppression for typed
#        overlapping-box filtering)
#     7. gofaces filters by typed confidence + class-probability
#        thresholds (typed env-driven via typed
#        `YOLO_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD` + typed
#        `YOLO_PROBA_THRESHOLD`)
#     8. gofaces prints typed `[x y w h confidence class]` typed
#        bounding-box predictions to stdout +
#     9. optionally writes a typed bounding-box mask PNG to
#        `--output`
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from `cmd/main.go` stdlib
#                       `flag.<Type>(...)` declarations +
#                       `envconfig.Process("yolo", &config)`
#                       env-driven config;  extracted via raw
#                       fetch of `cmd/main.go`)
#
#   gofaces [FLAGS...]
#
#   Flags:
#     --model <PATH>                  path to the ONNX model file
#                                     (default `../model/
#                                     model.onnx`)
#     --img <PATH>                    path to the input JPEG
#                                     image (default `../samples/
#                                     olivier.wulveryck.jpg`)
#     --output <PATH>                 path of an output PNG mask
#                                     (empty means no file)
#     -s                              silent mode (useful if
#                                     output is `-`)
#     -h                              show help (with env-var
#                                     listing from typed
#                                     `envconfig.Usage`)
#
#   Environment variables (envconfig prefix `yolo`):
#     YOLO_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD       confidence threshold
#                                     (default 0.10; REQUIRED)
#     YOLO_PROBA_THRESHOLD            class-probability
#                                     threshold (default 0.90;
#                                     REQUIRED)
